G-20 Vows ‘Strong’ Response to Slowing Economy

-- B y   S i m o n   K e n n e d y
-- 
2011-09-23T02:18:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-23/g-20-pledge-strong-response-to-slowing-economy.html
Finance chiefs from the Group of 20
nations said they will address “renewed challenges” facing the
slowing global economy.  In a statement released after talks in  Washington , the
officials said they were “committed to a strong and coordinated
international response to address the renewed challenges facing
the global economy, notably from heightened
downside risks from sovereign stresses, financial system
fragility, market turbulence, weak economic growth and
unacceptably high unemployment.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Simon Kennedy in Washington at 
